saloon /səˈluːn/

(saloons) 

1. N-COUNT A saloon is a car with seats for four or more people, a fixed roof, and a boot that is separate from the part of the car that you sit in. 箱式小货车 [英国英语] 

2. N-COUNT A saloon is a place where alcoholic drinks are sold and drunk. 酒馆 [美国英语] [老式] 

例： In the saloon, he drank whisky and let his eyes become accustomed to the dimness. 在酒馆里，他喝了威士忌，双眼也变得适应昏暗。

